OUT! LBW! Shoaib Bashir takes the sixth and final wicket. That was plumb! Tossed up full and on middle, spins in. Chivanga misses a straight line as he looks to defend. An appeal for LBW but turned down somehow. England take the review and rightfully gets the decision. THREE REDS on Ball Tracking. A happy and comfortable win for England as they win by an innings and 45 runs.

FOUR! Chivanga is taking his chances! Fuller delivery on off, Chivanga skips down and smashes it through mid off for a boundary.
Flatter and around off, Chivanga plays the reverse hit very fine and to third man for a couple more.
FOUR! Lofted away! Floats it full and outside off. Chivanga hits on the up, clears the man at cover and it races to the fence.

OUT! TAKEN! Flatter, on middle and leg, Blessing Muzarabani looks to heave it but mistimes his stroke completely. The ball goes in the air towards deep mid-wicket. Joe Root goes behind and takes an easy catch. Zimbabwe go seven down now.

OUT! TIMBER! Shoaib Bashir strikes again! Touch short, outside off and it turns in a long way. Tafadzwa Tsiga looks to push it but gets beaten as the ball clips the top of leg. A bit of confusion as the umpires go upstairs to have a look. The replays show that the ball had clearly clipped the leg pole.

Ben Stokes has his mouth wide open. What a catch!

The onfield decision stands and that is the end of a brave innings from Sean Williams!

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant from Josh Tongue and Ben Stokes! The field placement has paid off on the very next delivery. TAKEN! The short ball ploy with a short leg works straight away! Oh, hang on, the celebrations will have to wait as the front foot is being checked. Would you believe it? Josh Tongue has overstepped. Ollie Pope had been brought in at short leg just before this ball. Brian Bennett tried to fend it but the ball got big on him and it went to the left of Pope, who dived to snaffle it one-handed. FOUR and that will be HUNDRED for Brian Bennett! 2nd Test ton for Bennett and this has been a knock of the highest order. On a back of a length, on off, Brian Bennett waits on the back foot and uses the pace by opening the bat face. Steers it to the left of gully and it races away for a boundary. Takes the helmet off and soaks in all the applause from the Trent Bridge crowd. Brings up his century in 97 balls and this is the fastest century in Tests by a Zimbabwean batter.

FOUR! Two in two but this is even better! Full and at the stumps, Brian Bennett presents the full face of the bat and just eases himself into the drive. Plays it to the left of mid on for a boundary to get to 99.
FOUR! Fine shot! On a back of a length, around off, Brian Bennett gets on his toes and punches it through covers for a boundary.

On a back of a length, outside off, Raza lets it be.
Short of a length, on middle-leg, Brian Bennett looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the back thigh.

DROPPED AGAIN! Second dropped catch of the over. This was the easier of the two and it is Joe Root who has shelled this opportunity. On a back of a length, on off, Brian Bennett hops but stays leg side of the ball to defend. Does not quite cover the line of the ball and the outside edge is found. It goes at a good height around the waist towards Root at first slip but the ball goes through his hands and goes behind for a couple of runs.
Ben Stokes starts with a short of a length ball, outside off, Brian Bennett leaves it alone to the keeper. Uh oh! Umpire signals that it's a NO BALL!

DROPPED! Shoaib Bashir fails to cling on. Floats it up, full and on off, Sikandar Raza skips down the track to push it down the ground. Chips it to the right of Bashir who dives but the ball clips him on the fingertips and goes behind. They cross.
Pushed across from around the wicket, on a length, Brian Bennett lunges and drives it past cover for a single.
Back of a length, spinning into the right-hander, Sikandar Raza rocks back and flicks it to short fine leg.
Tosses it up, full and on off, Sikandar Raza knocks it to mid off.
Full, outside off. Brian Bennett drives it to cover.
Good length, on the off stump. Sikandar Raza works it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on the off stump, Sikandar Raza guides it to mid-wicket.
Full, outside the off stump. Sikandar Raza uses his feet and drives it back to the bowler.
On a length, just outside off, Sikandar Raza looks to play but decides to leave it at the last minute and chops it towards backward point.
From over the wicket, on a good length, on off, Sikandar Raza defends it back to the bowler.
Pushed through, on a length, on middle, Brian Bennett nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tosses up, on the middle and leg, Brian Bennett tucks it straight to square leg.
Turning into the pads, Sikandar Raza flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Sikandar Raza pushes it to cover.
Slows it down and pulls the length back slightly, on off, Sikandar Raza smothers the spin by getting on the front foot.
Tosses it up, full and on off, Sikandar Raza drives it back to Bashir.
On a length, outside off, Brian Bennett drives it to the right of cover where Ben Stokes dives and stops it.
On a bit full length, on middle and off, Brian Bennett looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.

FOUR! Gets it through! On a good length, around off, Brian Bennett waits on it and plays it late. Uses the pace of the ball by opening the bat face and guides it between gully and backward point for four more.
On a good length, targeting the stumps, jags back in and Brian Bennett looks to defend it and gets an inside edge back on the pads.

FOUR! Sumptuous! Cook hurls it slightly on the fuller side, around off, Brian Bennett plants his front foot ahead and does not try to overhit this one. Just times the drive to the right of mid off for a boundary.
From over the wicket, on a length, outside off, Brian Bennett drives it to mid on.
This drifts away slightly, on a length, outside off, Sikandar Raza lunges to block. Gets it off the outer half to backward point.
On a full length, outside off, Sikandar Raza uses his feet and drives it straight to cover.
Tosses it up, full and at the stumps, driven to mid on.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! First, Craig Ervine and now, Sean Williams, Shoaib Bashir gets both experienced southpaws. Bashir drags the length back and keeps the line around off, Williams hangs back and tries to glide it with an open bat face past first slip. Plays a bit outside the line of the ball. It catches the inside edge and crashes back onto the stumps. Sean goes for 25 (41). Zimbabwe are now 156/3, trailing by 409 runs.
Sean Williams b S Bashir 25 (41b 4x4 0x6)
FOUR! Hit with real authority! Loopy delivery, on off, Sean Williams reaches out in front and nails the sweep through square leg for a boundary.
Floated up, full and on off, Sean Williams gets forward to defend.
Short length, on off, Sean Williams tucks it towards deep square leg for a single.
On a back of a length, on off, guided to point.
On a length, outside off, Sean Williams defends it towards point.
Good length, on off, Sean Williams pats it to mid on.
On a good length, angling back on to the stumps, Sean Williams pushes it from the crease and gets it off the shoulder of the bat. But lands safely in the backward point region.
From around the wicket, on a length, on middle, Sean Williams clips it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Swept away! Brian Bennett collects his 15th boundary of his innings! Full on middle, Brian Bennett sits on one knee and sweep this one behind square, through the backward square leg region for four.
Tosses up, on off, Brian Bennett lunges forward and defends it back at the bowler.
FOUR! Short and cut away! Short on off, Brian Bennett cuts it through the vacant point region for four.
A touch shorter on middle, Brian Bennett flicks it to short mid-wicket.
On a full length, just around the fourth stump, Sean Williams rocks back and cuts it away to point for a single.

Full, just outside off, Brian Bennett drives this one through backward point region. The short third man fielder runs to his right and dives to save the ball, and manages to get a hand to it as it slows down the speed of the ball. Batters still run three for it.
Back of a length, outside off, angling into the batter, Sean Williams pats it towards backward point.
A bit full in length, on the off stump line, Sean Williams defends off the back foot to cover.
FOUR! Nicely done! Second boundary of the over! Length ball outside off, Sean Williams steers it past backward point for four.
A bit fuller, on the off stump line, Sean Williams pokes and gets beaten on the outside edge as there was some extra bounce on that ball.
On a good length, on to the stumps. Coming into the left-hander with the angle. Sean Williams tucks it to midwicket.

FOUR! Easy pickings for Sean Williams! Length ball on the pads, Sean Williams flicks it behind square to the right of deep fine leg for four. Ben Duckett runs across the turf to cut it off and puts in a dive near the boundary, but doesn't manage to stop it.
Short and sliding down leg, Brian Bennett leaves it alone.
On a short length, outside off. Sean Williams cuts this one from the backfoot towards point for a single.
Slower through the air, fuller, on off, Sean Williams leans forward and drives it to short cover.
Short on off, Sean Williams hangs back and slaps it to short cover.
Slower through the air. On a full length, outside off, Sean Williams looks to sweep it but gets an edge onto the pads and the ball balloons towards first slip.
Short on middle, Brian Bennett works it square of the wicket to deep square leg for a single.
Sam Cook comes around the stumps, on a back of a length, outside off, Sean Williams guides it towards backward point.
Back of a length, outside off. Brian Bennett works it to fine leg for a single.

Four! Lucky for Brian Bennett as that ball goes through the vacant third slip region. Length ball that swings away, Brian Bennett throws his bat at it as he looks to drive it and gets a thick outside edge that goes through the third slip region for four.
A loose shot but Brian Bennett gets away with it! On a back of a length, seaming away, outside off, Brian Bennett goes feeling for it but is lucky not to nick this one behind.
This time back of a length, just around the off stump line. Brian Bennett gets beaten in defence as the ball hits him high on the thigh pad.
From over the wicket, Sam Cook starts with a good length ball, outside off. Brian Bennett pushes it to point.
Full on off, Sean Williams drives it straight to mid off.
On a full length, on off. Sean Williams sweeps it to the short fine leg fielder.
Tossed up just outside off, Sean Williams prods forward and defends it.
A touch short, on off, Sean Williams cuts it to backward point.
Flighted, just outside off, Sean Williams pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Sean Williams blocks it off the front foot.
On a full length, hitting the off stump line, Brian Bennett defends it right under his eyes.
FOUR! Another beautiful shot from Brian Bennett! This was on middle, but wasn't that full to be driven. But Brian Bennett manages to drive it with good balance, down the ground for four.
Back of a length, outside off. Brian Bennett drives this one straight to the extra cover fielder.
FOUR! Well controlled pull shot from Brian Bennett! Short ball on middle, Brian Bennett takes it on as he pulls it in front of square for a one bounce four.
Brilliant one from Josh Tongue! Back of a length, around the off stump. Brian Bennett gets squared up in defence as he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short length, angling down the leg side. Brian Bennett looks to flick it but misses it to the keeper.
FOUR! A touch short and on the pads, Sean Williams whips it off the back foot, behind square, towards the deep backward square leg region for four.
Tosses it up, just outside off, Sean Williams defends it on the front foot.
Full on middle , Brian Bennett drives it to long on for a single.
Overpitched on off, Brian Bennett drives it to short cover.
Tad full length wide outside off. Brian Bennett drives it through the left of covers and gets a couple of runs.
Tossed up off break on off, Brian Bennett defends it off the front foot.
Short length, into the body, Brian Bennett tucks it to the left of short fine leg for a single.
Short in length, on the stumps. Sean Williams flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Sean Williams gets on top of the bounce and works it behind point for a couple of runs.
Full length, on the pads, Brian Bennett clips it to the square leg region for a single.
Touch full length, on the stumps. Brian Bennett pushes it straight to mid on.

FOUR! Lovely from Brian Bennett! That will be the third Test FIFTY for Brian Bennett! Half volley on off, Brian Bennett eases the drive through the vacant extra cover region for four. Bennett will be looking to convert this into a big score.
Again a tossed up delivery on off, Sean Williams plays the push drive off the front foot, back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Sean Williams pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Brian Bennett drives this one through covers. But now there's a protection in the deep as the deep extra cover fielder stops the ball. Single taken.
A touch fuller on off, Brian Bennett nicely prods forward and defends it.
Shorter, off break on off, stays low. Brian Bennett manages to get his bat down in time as the ball takes the bottom edge and goes on the bounce to the first slip fielder.
Short on middle, Brian Bennett rocks back and pulls it fiercely to the left of short mid-wicket, where Ben Stokes makes a good save.
Full on off, Sean Williams drives it to short covers.

Short ball, on middle, Sean Williams looks to duck under it and can't get out of the way, as the ball hits him on the helmet. Oh, that would have hurt. Josh Tongue walks up to him to check. Sean Williams says he is okay. A mandatory concussion test will follow.
Full on off, Sean Williams drives it down the ground, without much feet movement. The catching mid off fielder runs behind it and cuts it off. Two runs taken.
Length again, in the channel outside off, Sean Williams shoulders his arms to it.
Length ball that seams into the left hander, Sean Williams must have thought it would go away and hence he left it, but the ball comes back in, and goes over the off stump.
From round the wicket, Back of a length delivery, outside off, Sean Williams leaves it alone.
Overpitched on middle, Sean Williams flicks it to the left of mid on for a single.
Slower through the air, shorter on middle, Sean Williams blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Superb delivery by Shoaib Bashir! Slower through the air, tossed up, on middle, the ball drifts into the left hander before turning away, after pitching. Craig Ervine is drawn into the front foot defensive shot as he prods at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes low towards first slip, where Harry Brook takes a good low catch. They are checking if the catch is clean. Here's the slow-motion version of it. The fingers are clearly under the ball as Harry Brook took the catch. Craig Ervine has to go. Sean Williams is the new batter.
Craig Ervine (c) c H Brook b S Bashir 42 (64b 6x4 0x6)
Full delivery, around off, Craig Ervine defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on middle, Craig Ervine works it off the back foot to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, Craig Ervine goes on the back foot and steers it to backward point.
Full toss on off, Brian Bennett drives it back to the bowler.
Short ball sliding down leg, Brian Bennett goes for the pull, but can't connect.
Full on off, Craig Ervine plays this one, to the left of short cover for a single.
Fuller and swinging away, Craig Ervine again looks to drive it through covers and again gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short ball, well outside off, Craig Ervine leaves it alone. Jamie Smith the keeper does well to jump up high and collect the ball one handed well over his head.

FOUR! Lucky for Craig Ervine that there's no third slip! Full delivery from round the wicket, angling in and then swings away, Craig Ervine looks to drive it and gets a thick edge that flies wide of the 2nd slip fielder for four.
Flighted delivery on off, Brian Bennett hangs back and blocks it under his eyes.
FOUR! Another one driven through covers! Tossed up on off, Brian Bennett's eyes light up again seeing the tossed up delivery, as he drives this sweetly through extra covers for four.
Better from Shoaib Bashir! a touch shorter, off break, that turns in on middle, Brian Bennett defends it solidly off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Full on off, Brian Bennett drives this through extra covers for four.

Tossed up above the eye line, on off, Craig Ervine drives this to mid off, who puts in a slide to save the ball and the ball goes through him. Then the fielder gets up and cuts it off near the boundary. Batters run three. Ben Duckett is the culprit.
Tossed up on middle, Brian Bennett flicks it off the front foot to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Punched! Length ball outside off, Craig Ervine sees the width on offer and punches it off the middle of the bat through the point region for four.
Full and on the pads, Brian Bennett flicks it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, Brian Bennett pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length on off, Brian Bennett stays back and blocks it into the ground.
Full on middle, Brian Bennett square drives it to backward point, who makes a good save.
Length ball on off, Brian Bennett defends it under his eyes. Josh Tongue has overstepped. It's a NO BALL.
Length ball sliding down leg, Brian Bennett looks to tickle it fine, but doesn't get any bat on it.
Short and wide outside off, Craig Ervine is happy to let it go.
A touch shorter on off, Craig Ervine hangs back and blocks it under his eyes as the ball goes on the bounce to forward short leg.
Full on middle, Craig Ervine pushes it towards mid on.
Overpitched on off, Craig Ervine eases the drive to short cover.
Slower through the air, flighted delivery, full, just outside off, Craig Ervine drives it off the outer half of the bat to point.
Tossed up, off break on off, Craig Ervine defends it off the front foot.

Beats the outside edge. On a good length, just in the channel of the outside off stump. Brian Bennett pokes at it from the crease and gets beaten on the outside edge to the keeper. It's LUNCH BREAK on Day 2!
Fuller in length, on off, Craig Ervine gets on the front foot and eases it to the left of cover for a single.
Good length, just outside off. Craig Ervine defends it to point.
Lands it on a nagging length, on off, Craig Ervine guides it to point.
On a full length, on the off stump. Craig Ervine pushes it through mid on, and the fielder there gives it a chase and keeps it to two.

Josh Tongue bends his back and digs it in short, at the left shoulder of the batter. The ball gets big on Ervine as he tries to fend it down. The ball goes past the gloves and catches him on the left shoulder.
Loopy delivery, tempting the batter to go for the big shot, on off, Brian Bennett resists and drives it along the ground to mid off.
Appeal for LBW but not given. On a full length, on the stumps. Brian Bennett looks to defend it, but it goes past the inside edge and hits the front pad.
Fractionally short, on off, Brian Bennett goes right back in his crease to defend.
Drifting into the right-hander, on the pads, worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air. Tosses it up on the stumps. Craig Ervine flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floated up, on off, driven to short cover.
On a length, on middle. Craig Ervine tucks it to the deep square leg region for a single.

FOUR! That could have gone to hand! On a back of a length, on middle, Craig Ervine hops and tries to tuck it across the line with a closed bat face. Gets an inside edge onto the back thigh pad and lobs towards the slip cordon. It drops wide of the diving gully fielder to his right and goes behind for a boundary.
On a full length, on off. Craig Ervine looks to clip it to the leg side but gets a leading edge to Crawley at gully on the bounce.
On a nagging length, just outside the off stump, Craig Ervine is caught in the crease and defends inside the line to get beaten.
This time a bit full in length, on the pads. Craig Ervine looks to clip it but misses it and wears it on the front pad. Certainly going down the leg stump.
Attacking the stumps, on a good length from around the wicket, Craig Ervine tucks it to mid-wicket.
Drags the length back and gets a bit of turn, on off, Brian Bennett presses back to block.
On full length, on off. Brian Bennett prods forwards and defends it.
Loopy delivery, very full, on the pads, Brian Bennett fails to flick it away and wears it on the front pad.
Slows it down, full and on off, Craig Ervine pushes it to the right of point and takes a quick single.
Tosses up, full, on off. Craig Ervine defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! A freebie and Craig Ervine accepts it gleefully! A loosener first up from Bashir. Low full toss, outsie off, Ervine feasts on it as he creams the drive through extra cover for a boundary.
Bit of an extra bounce on that one. On a good length, just outside off. Brian Bennett looks to punch it off the back foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Attacking the off pole, on a good length, Brian Bennett covers the line and keeps it out.
On a length, around the fifth stump, Craig Ervine prods forward to defend it and gets a thick inside edge to square leg. Single taken.
Drags the length back but keeps the line around off, Craig Ervine punches it to point.
On a good length, on off. Craig Ervine blocks it towards the point region.
On a hard length, on off, steered to gully.
On a full length, on middle, and off. Brian Bennett works it straight towards the mid-wicket fielder.

A loud shout for LBW but there was a woody sound! Slanting into the right-hander, on a good length, on middle, Brian Bennett does not move his feet much and looks to clip it away. Gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length, outside off. Moving away from the batter. Brian Bennett leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a good length, around off, Brian Bennett dabs it down on the off side.

FOUR! Oh, my word! Perilously close to the leg stump! This moves back late into the right-hander, on a length, on middle and leg, Brian Bennett gets his front pad out of the way to get the bat out in front. Looks to push it down the ground with a straight bat. Gets an inside edge that sneaks through the gap between the bat and the pad to go past the leg stump.
On a back of a length, on off, Brian Bennett stabs it down on the off side.
On a short length, wide outside off, Craig Ervine leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a short of a length, on off, Craig Ervine rides the bounce and steers it to gully.
On a short length, outside off, Craig Ervine gets on the top of the bounce and guides it straight to the point fielder.
On a short of a length, on the pads, glanced down to deep fine leg for one.
On a good length, just outside the off stump. Craig Ervine punches it to the right of cover for a single.
On a back of a length, on off, Craig Ervine hops and pats it down on the leg side. Gus Atkinson falls over on his follow-through but gets back up quickly.
On a good length, just outside off. Brian Bennett looks to defend and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Sliding onto the pads, on a length, Craig Ervine wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, just on off. Craig Ervine defends it towards the point region.
In and around the off stump, on a good length, solidly kept out by Ervine.
Sam Cook comes around the wicket, on a good length, targeting the off stump. Craig Ervine plays it with soft hands towards gully.

50 UP FOR ZIMBABWE! On a length, at the stumps, Brian Bennett gives the bowler the charge and swipes it through mid-wicket. The ball does not have enough legs to reach the fence and it is cut off by the chasing fielder. Three more runs for Brian.
On a full length, just outside off, Craig Ervine gets a little bit of width and drives it to the right of the bowler. The fielder at mid off gives it a chase and keeps it to two.
Full and straight, knocked to mid on with a straight bat.
On a good length, just outside the off stump. Craig Ervine blocks it.

Oh, this kept low! On a back of a length, on off, Craig Ervine hops to deal with it but the ball does not rise as much as Ervine expected it to. Sneaks under the blade and goes over the top of the stumps. It dies down on its way to the keeper.
On a good length, on off. Craig Ervine pushes it towards the covers region.
On a back of a length, nipping back in, on off, Brian Bennett gets on top of the bounce and punches it through covers. Ollie Pope goes after it and mops it up. Three runs taken.

Brilliant delivery to end the over. On a length, just outside off, angling into the batter, Craig Ervine looks to defend it from the crease and gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball moves away off the deck.
Seaming away slightly, on a good length, on off, Craig Ervine gets forward to defend but gets it more of the outer half and it rolls towards gully.
On a full length, on off. Angling into the batter, Craig Ervine defends it solidly.
Tighter line on off, on a good length, Craig Ervine lets it be.
FOUR! Easy as you like! Cook errs in line as he offers width, on a short of a length, Craig Ervine stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary.
A bit too straight, on the pads, Brian Bennett is late on the tickle and ekes out an inside edge onto the pads. It dribbles towards deep fine leg for one.
On a length, on the off stump line, Craig Ervine looks to flick it but gets it off the inner half of the blade and it rolls in front of square leg.
On a length, going across, Craig Ervine lets it be.

FOUR! Not quite from the middle of the bat but Craig Ervine has his first boundary! Angling away from the batter, on a length, Ervine goes after it as he commits to the drive. Gets it off the outer half of the bat past backward point for a boundary.
Going across the batter, on a back of a length, Craig Ervine leaves it alone.
On a full length, on the stumps, Craig Ervine defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off, Craig Ervine lunges to block.
On a good length, on off. Coming into the left-hander, Craig Ervine tucks it down to deep backward square leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off, Craig Ervine pokes at the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pitches it on a full length, just outside off. Craig Ervine steers it past backward point for a couple of runs and gets off the mark.

OUT! CAUGHT! 'Catch it' is the cry and it is taken! Sam Cook has his first Test wicket. Stays around the wicket and lands it on a good length, on the off stump line, Ben Curran walks across slightly and tries to get behind the line of the ball. Gets his bat out in front to defend. The ball nips away off the deck to square him up in defence. The outside edge is found and Harry Brook takes it safely at second slip to his right.
Ben Curran c H Brook b S Cook 6 (10b 0x4 0x6)

Leading edge but it lands safely! On a full length, on middle and leg. Ben Curran closes the face of the bat a bit early as he looks to flick it towards the leg side. Gets a leading edge and it lobs over the bowler.
Slanting in, on a good length, around off, Ben Curran leaves it alone.
Nice delivery to end the over. On a full length, onto the stumps. Brian Bennett defends this one.

FOUR! Off the edge! On a back of a length, on off, Brian Bennett hangs back and tries to push it through the off side. This goes off the outside edge but all along the ground and races past gully to his right for a boundary.
On a length, just around the fifth stump line. Brian Bennett steers it towards point.

Lands it on a length, on off, Ben Curran knocks it down the ground. Does not quite get hold of it but manages to get it past mid off to his left. Josh Tongue gives it a chase and cuts it off. Three runs taken.
This time a bit full in length, onto the pads. Ben Curran tucks it down along the ground towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
On a good length, on middle, Ben Curran keeps it out on the leg side.

FOUR! Edged away! Cook goes full, outside off, Brian Bennett tries to cash in on the length and goes hard on the drive. Gets an outside edge that goes low and wide to the right of the diving third slip fielder for a boundary.
Zeroing in at the stumps, on a good length, Brian Bennett gets right behind the line and pats it down the deck.
From over the wicket, on a length, wide outside off, shaping away from the batter. Brian Bennett leaves it alone.
Leg bye! On middle and leg, on a nagging length, Ben Curran gets inside the line for the tickle but fails to lay any bat on it. The ball goes off the thigh pad towards deep fine leg for a leg bye.
On a good length, just around the off stump, angling into the left-hander. Ben Curran defends it to the left of the bowler.
Shaping away from the left-hander from around the wicket, on a length, Ben Curran makes a leave.
Short in length, angling into the batter, Brian Bennett pulls but gets a little bit late on it and hits it down towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Width offered and Brian Bennett cashes in! Short and wide on off, asking to be hit. Brian Bennett obliges as he slaps it off the back foot past backward point for a boundary.
Good length, just outside off, Brian Bennett leaves that one as well.

A loud shout for LBW but turned down! Seemed to be doing too much. Sliding onto the pads, on a length, Brian Bennett is beaten on the flick on the inside edge. The ball seams back in to go through and hit the front pad. Comfortably going down leg as the replays confirm.
Good length, just outside off. Brian Bennett leaves it alone.
Gus Atkinson starts on a short of a length, on a middle and leg. Ben Curran plays it to backward square leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Some movement on that one! On a back of a length, just around the off stump. Moving away from Brian Bennett, who gets beaten on the outside edge as he hops to deal with it.

FOUR! Hit with absolute authority! Full and moving away in the air, no half measures from Brian Bennett as he throws his hands at the ball and crunches the drive through covers for the third boundary in a row.

FOUR! Not convincing but Brian Bennett will take it! Pitched up, attacking the stumps, Brian Bennett jabs at the delivery with a straight bat. Ekes out a thickish outside edge that races through square leg for four more.

FOUR! That could have so easily gone back onto the stumps! On a length, just around the off stump, Brian Bennett tentatively hangs his bat out a bit away from his body to defend the ball. Gets an inside edge that sneaks past the stumps and beats the diving deep fine leg fielder to his right for a boundary.
On a full length, wide outside off, moving away from the batter, Brian Bennett leaves it alone to the keeper.
First ball for Sam Cook in Test cricket. From over the wicket, on a full length, on the pads, Brian Bennett flicks it straight to mid on

OUT! BOWLED! Blessing Muzarabani has the last laugh! Back of a length, just outside off, Harry Brook looks to cut it as he inside edges it and chops it back onto his stumps. And with that, England have declared!
