FOUR! Harry Brook's in a hurry here! Full on middle, Harry Brook skips down the track and lofts it over mid on. The mid on fielder goes running behind the ball and tries to push the ball away from the ropes, near the boundary, but fails to do so.

SIX! Harry Brook gets to his FIFTY in style! Short ball, just outside off, Harry Brook picks it up from there and pulls it way over deep backward square leg for six. An enterprising knock so far from Brook.

Dropped! Tafadzwa Tsiga the wicket-keeper has shelled a rather easy chance. A touch fuller, and shaping away, outside off, drawing the batter into the shot. Jamie Smith goes feeling at it as he outside edges it to the right of the wicket-keeper, who takes a step to his right and gets a good right hand on it, but can't quite hang on to it.
On a good length, wide outside off. Shaping away from the right-hander, Jamie Smith thinks to go after it but leaves it alone in the end.
FOUR!  What a shot from Jamie Smith to get off the mark! Full and on the pads, Jamie Smith clips it off the middle of the bat, as the ball goes on the bounce over deep mid-wicket fence.
On back of a length, just outside off. Harry Brook works it towards third man for a run.
Dug in short, on off, Harry Brook pulls it in front of square to the left of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
From over the wicket, on good length, on off. Harry Brook guides it towards backward point.
On a full length, outside the off. Jamie Smith leans forward and drives it to the left of the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Short ball that rises viciously on Ben Stokes who is absolutely taken aback by this short ball as he takes his eyes off the ball. The ball takes the top edge and goes high in the air towards deep fine leg, where Ben Curran settles under it and takes a very good catch.
Ben Stokes (c) c B Curran b B Muzarabani 9 (13b 1x4 0x6)
On a length, around off, Harry Brook tucks it down to mid-wicket for a single.
This time on a length, just around the off stump. Ben Stokes opens his arms and cuts it through deep point for a single.
On a full length, outside off. Harry Brook drives it to mid off for a single.
From over the wicket, on a good length, just outside off. Harry Brook defends it to the right of the bowler.
Back of a length and wide outside off, Harry Brook steers it down to the third man fielder for a single.

FOUR! Now Harry Brook's adding salt to the wound! Back of a length, outside off, Harry Brook cuts it fiercely, square of the wicket through the point region for four. Wow, that went to the boundary very quickly.

Dropped and FOUR! Short ball just outside off, Harry Brook plays the upper cut and hits it to the left of deep third man, who runs to his left and gets to the ball, but the ball goes through his hands and hits the boundary ropes on the bounce. It's the substitute fielder Wellington Masakadza who is the culprit.
This time a back of the hand slower short ball, banged into the pitch, on off, Harry Brook pulls it along the ground to the left of deep square leg. Two runs taken.
Short ball that goes easily over the batter's head. Wide given.
From round the wicket, short ball on off, Ben Stokes pulls it along the ground to deep square leg. Singe taken.
Back of a length on middle, Harry Brook works it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.

Full, almost a yorker, just outside off, Harry Brook looks to defend it off the crease, as the ball takes the inside edge and trundles to his right. Ben Stokes calls for a single, and Harry Brook obliges. End of an expensive over.
Length delivery, Harry Brook skips down the track and drives it back to the bowler, who fails to collect it on the bounce as the ball ricochets off his hands into the leg side.
Full on middle, Harry Brook pushes it to mid on.

SIX! And again! Same ball, same shot, same result! Short ball on leg, Harry Brook just helps it on its way as he pulls it over deep fine leg region for six. Remember, there was a fielder stationed there and Brook took him on and cleared him easily.
SIX! Short ball on off, Harry Brook pulls this easily over deep square leg for six.
Full ball angling into right hander and straightens after pitching, in the channel outside off. Harry Brook looks to defend it as the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short ball on off, Harry Brook pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Harry Brook on the charge! Length delivery, shaping away, outside off, Harry Brook charges down the track and lofts it over mid off for four.
FOUR! Cut away! Back of a length, outside off, Harry Brook stands tall and cuts it in front of square for four.
Now a full toss, well outside off, this time Stokesy drives it off the middle, as he plays it to the right of deep cover for a single.
Another full delivery, well outside off, Ben Stokes square drives this off the toe end of the bat as the ball goes to the point fielder.
Full and outside off, Ben Stokes drives this sweetly but it goes straight to the point fielder.
Back of a length and outside off, Ben Stokes pushes it to the left of point for a single to keep the strike.

Back of a length outside off. Seeing the width on offer, Ben Stokes's eyes light up as he goes for the cut, but Blessing Muzarabani's natural height provides him extra bounce and hence Stokes is beaten on the outside edge as the ball goes over his willow.
Length ball moving a touch, outside off. This time Ben Stokes leaves it alone.

Wow! Length delivery angling away, as it pitches on middle and moves away, just outside off. Ben Stokes premeditated the shot a bit as he wanted to work it into the leg side. But then he understood the line was a bit outside off and hence he sort of curbed the stroke last moment.

FOUR! Cracking drive from Ben Stokes through covers! Full and just outside off, Ben Stokes drives this with full extension of the arms as he beautifully swings through the line. The ball goes through the covers region for four.
Length ball shaping in a touch, in the channel outside off, Ben Stokes shoulders his arms to that one.

Back of a length on middle leg, Harry Brook looks to work it into the leg side and misses it yet again. Oh goodness, he is not been able to play this flick of the length delivery for some time now as he gets beaten for the nth time and the ball hits him high on the front pad.
Overpitched, almost a yorker on off. Harry Brook pushes it to the left of the bowler, who dives to his left and makes the save.
Full and swinging into the left hander. Some late movement in the air. Ben Stokes comfortably flicks it to deep square leg for a single to get off the mark.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant from Zimbabwe! They have the first wicket of the morning and it's a beauty from Tanaka Chivanga! Ollie Pope's wonderful 171-run knock comes to an end! A touch full, in the channel outside off, shaping away from the right hander. Pope goes feeling at it, without any feet movement as the ball takes the outside edge and the keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga does the rest as he takes a fairly easy catch. Oh, then, Ollie is going for the review. He is not sure if he hit that. Here's the third umpire on screen. UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball goes past the bat and the on-field call stays.
Ollie Pope c T Tsiga b T Chivanga 171 (166b 24x4 2x6)
Length delivery sliding on the pads, Harry Brook misses the flick as the ball again hits his front pad and drops into the leg side. Batters sneak in a leg bye. Oh, its a NO BALL.
Back of a length again on leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it, but can't connect, as the ball hits him high on the front pad, near the thigh guard area.
Single taken and that brings up 500 for England. This is a back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Ollie Pope pushes it to the right of short mid-wicket and calls for one.

Good length on middle, Harry Brook just taps at it beside the pitch on the leg side and calls for a single. But Blessing Muzarabani was quick to run at the ball and avoid the single. Good first over then from Blessing Muzarabani!
Length ball on off, Harry Brook defends it to the point fielder.
Now goes the other way. Length delivery, shaping away a touch, outside off, Harry Brook goes feeling at it as he pushes at it. The ball swings away past his outside edge to the keeper.

Good ball! A touch fuller, swinging in a bit, Harry Brook looks to flick it, but gets beaten as the ball hits him high on the knee roll of his front pad. A bit of an appeal there, but more in hope as it must have been sliding down leg.
Length ball on off, slightly angling into the right hander, on off, Harry Brook blocks it comfortably, back to the bowler.
First runs of the day, straightaway. Blessing Muzarabani starts with a back of a length delivery on middle, Ollie Pope works it into the leg side towards the deep square leg fielder for one.

FOUR! Easy pickings and that sums up the day for Zimbabwe! A touch full sliding down leg, Harry Brook tickles it fine as the ball races away to the fence towards deep fine leg. That will be Stumps on Day 1.
Short on middle, Ollie Pope pulls it behind square to the right of deep backward point for a single.
Yorker outside off, Ollie Pope digs it out as he looks to drive it.
Back of a length delivery, that nips back into the right hander. Ollie Pope looks to push it but gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball goes over the off stump.
Length ball on middle, Ollie Pope works it to short mid-wicket.
Yorker on leg stump, Harry Brook looks to flick it and misses ast the ball hits his toe and goes into the leg side. Batters take a single.
Full and swinging on middle, Ollie Pope looks to flick it and gets a bit of an inside edge that hits his pads and goes into the ground.
Short ball on middle, Harry Brook pulls it square of the wicket to deep square leg for a single.
Full again, outside off, Ollie Pope drives it off the front foot to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Poor from Blessing Muzarabani! Ollie Pope gives it the full treatment! Length ball wide outside off, Ollie Pope slaps it in front of square to pick up his twenty-fourth four of the day.
Length ball that skids off the surface, outside off, Ollie Pope has a slash at it, but the ball takes the underedge and rolls towards gully.

Peach of a delivery from Blessing Muzarabani! Back of a length angled into the right hander, in the channel outside off, Ollie Pope looks to defend it off the back foot, as the ball straightens just enough to beat the outside edge on its way to the keeper.
Full on middle, Harry Brook clips it on the bounce to the right of mid on who dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Length again, on off, Harry Brook is right behind the line of that ball as he defends it off the front foot to mid off.
Length ball just outside off, Harry Brook punches it past the short cover fielder and picks up two runs.
Length ball, swinging into the right hander, Harry Brook defends it off the front foot. That was the not defended convincingly by Harry Brook!
Overpitches on middle, Ollie Pope swings through the line as the ball hits the inside half of his bat and goes along the ground to the left of deep fine leg for a single.
Fuller delivery sliding on the pads, Ollie Pope misses out on it, as he looks to flick it and gets an inside edge that ricochets onto his pads.
Length ball, swinging into the right hander, Harry Brook this time defends it solidly off the front foot.

Oh! That's a close leave from Harry Brook! He would say he judged the line well but that ball was very close to the off stump. Length ball angled in, around off, Harry Brook shoulders his arms to that one, as the ball goes over the off stump. Ahh, Blessing Muzarabani's natural bounce took it over the sticks.
Length ball, well outside off, Harry Brook gets his bat out of the way as he lets it go.
Length ball on off, Harry Brook blocks it to mid off.
A touch fuller and angling in, outside off, Harry Brook judges the line well and lets it go. That one rose quite a bit as it went to the wicket-keeper, who collected it over his head.
Back of a length, hint of shape away from the right hander, but the line is well outside off. Harry Brook leaves it alone.
Full and swinging in, but the line is on the leg stump, Harry Brook flicks it easily to deep fine leg for a single.
Full and sliding on the pads, Ollie Pope flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball swinging into the rhight hander, Ollie Pope blocks it off the inner half of the bat.
Length ball on off, Harry Brook plays it off the crease to the right of point for a single.
Full on middle, Harry Brook flicks it to short mid-wicket.

Length ball sliding on pads, Ollie Pope looks to flick it but misses it, as the ball hits his thigh pad and trundles along the ground in the direction of fine leg. The wicket-keeper runs behind it and cuts it off.
Length ball around off, Harry Brook opens the bat face and guides it to point.
Length ball angling in on middle, Harry Brook defends it off the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT! Blessing Muzarabani has a wicket! It's the big wicket of Joe Root! Zimbabwe have something to celebrate! Attempted short ball on off, Joe Root looks to hook it over deep fine leg, but doesn't really get on top of the bounce. Only manages to get height on the ball due to the top edge and ends up giving a simple catch to Sean Williams at deep fine leg.
Joe Root c S Williams b B Muzarabani 34 (44b 3x4 0x6)
Good length, around off, Ollie Pope cuts it towards backward point for a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Joe Root nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, just outside off, Ollie Pope looks to steer it past the gully fielder and plays it to the left of him. The fielder saves the ball but misfields it a bit. The batters take a single.
Length ball, that swings into the right hander a bit, on off, Joe Root nicely gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it under his eyes.
Length ball on off, Ollie Pope slashes it behind square towards the wide third man fielder for a single.
Length ball, outside off, moving away, Ollie Pope looks to guide it towards third man and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball angled into the right hander, Ollie Pope flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Length ball, just outside off, Ollie Pope looks to square drive it, but gets a bit of an underedge on it.

SIX! Picked up beautifully! Not the greatest of the balls from Victor Nyauchi bowls this one wide down leg, Ollie Pope goes for the flick as it's more of a chip shot that goes over deep fine leg for six. For a moment, one thought deep fine leg was in business.

Overpitched on middle leg, Ollie Pope now manages to flick it wide of the mid on fielder. The mid on fielder puts in a chase and manages to use his left leg to stop the ball right near the boundary. Batters run three!
FOUR! Ollie Pope is toying with the Zimbabwean bowlers now! Back of a length ball on off, Ollie Pope crouches and upper cuts it over the slip cordon for four.
FOUR! Lovely placement! Full again, no movement, on off, Ollie Pope drives this square of the wicket, wide of the extra cover fielder for four.
Back of a length ball on middle leg, Joe Root works it off the back foot into the leg side to the right of short mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length on off, Joe Root hops on the back foot and taps the ball into the ground.
FOUR! Back of a length, just outside off, Joe Root plays a controlled cut shot behind square to the left of deep point for four.
FOUR! Ollie Pope is going berserk! Overpitched again, on middle, Ollie Pope clips this one over mid on to pick up his third boundary of the over.
Overpitched, half volley on off, Ollie Pope drives it crisply, but straight to short cover.
Now a length ball on middle, Ollie Pope looks to defend it and gets a bit of an inside edge that hits his pads and goes into the ground.
FOUR! No stopping for Ollie Pope! Full on middle and leg, Ollie Pope clips it over short mid-wicket for four.
Four! Classy from Ollie Pope! Overpitched on off, Ollie Pope straight drives it, showing the full face of the bat, as the ball races away for four.
With this single, Joe Root brings up 13,000 runs in Test cricket. What a player! Full and sliding down on leg, Joe flicks it behind square to deep fine leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, Ollie Pope works it off the crease to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Crunched through covers! Full on off, Ollie Pope drives it off the front foot through covers for four.
Length ball on middle, Ollie Pope works it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lucky for Ollie Pope! Length ball seaming in, on off, Ollie Pope looks to play the steer, but he gets an under edge on it and the ball runs away fine of the short third fielder for four.
Back of a length on off, Joe Root punches it to the left of short cover for a single.
short and outside off, Ollie Pope cuts it towards deep point for a single.
Full on middle and leg, Joe Root drives it to mid on.
Shorter on off, Joe Root pushes it to short cover.
Leg bye! Overpitched on leg, Ollie Pope goes for the flick and misses it. The ball goes off the pads past the keeper for a leg bye.
Shorter carrom ball, on off, Joe Root works it off the back foot, along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A touch short and quick on middle, Joe Root punches it to short cover.
Fuller on leg, Joe Root looks to flick it but can't get any bat, as the ball thuds into his pads. It was the carrom ball from Sikandar Raza.
Full again, on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it along the ground to short mid-wicket.
Full on off, Ollie Pope drives it straight to mid off.
FOUR! Freebie and dealt with by Ollie Pope! Full and sliding down leg, Ollie Pope flicks this along the ground through the mid-wicket region for four. No chance for deep square leg to cut it off.
Full and around off, Ollie Pope goes for the drive, but gets it off the toe end of the bat as he drives it straight to mid off.
Back of a length, well outside off, Joe Root plays the steer to deep third man for a single.
Length ball on off, Joe Root blocks it off the front foot.

Short on middle, Ollie Pope pushes it to short mid-wicket. Joe Root calls for a single and was almost half way down. Ollie Pope sent him back and Root just about got back in time as he put in a desperate dive. Direct hit there would have been interesting.
Carrom ball, a touch short, turning away, a bit, just outside off, Joe Root defends it off the front foot.
A touch fuller, Ollie Pope still manages to cut it off the back foot, as he plays it along the ground to deep extra cover for a single.
Overpitched on off, Ollie Pope drives it to the right of mid off, who puts in a dive and saves potentially four runs.
FOUR! Short and put away! Carrom ball from Sikandar Raza, shorter in length on off, Ollie Pope rocks on the back foot and cuts it in front of square for four.
Off break a touch full on middle leg, Ollie Pope drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller, shaping it in around the pads of the batter. Joe Root nudges it toward mid-wicket for no run.
On a length around off. Joe Root eases it out.
On a length, on the stumps. Ollie Pope walks down the track and tucks it toward leg side for one.

Slower now, back of a length, on off and middle Ollie Pope detects the short length and decides to go big but fails to judge the change of pace and misses on the inner edge. The ball catches him around the abdomen.
Good-length delivery, just outside off. Ollie Pope stabs it toward backward point.
On a length, around off. Ollie Pope keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Joe Root knocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on middle. Ollie Pope lunges and pushes it toward mid on for one.
Drags his length back, around off. Joe Root drags the pull toward deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on leg. Ollie Pope nudges it toward short fine leg for one.
Fuller, on the stumps. Joe Root drives it toward long on for a single.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Joe Root tucks it toward square leg for no run.
Short, on middle and leg. Joe Root stays back and nudges it toward his leg side for one.
FOUR! SHOT! Flat and short, outside off. Joe Root steers it with an open bat face toward the third man fence for another boundary.
Slower, fuller on the stumps. Ollie Pope paddles it toward fine leg and gets a single.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Joe Root flicks it toward square leg for one.

Shortish outside off. Ollie Pope cuts hard toward the gap at cover. However, the fielder at cover gets some hands on it, which slows the pace of the rolling ball. The fielder at wide mid off does well to have a chase and save the boundary. Three runs taken in between.
Fuller, on off and middle. Ollie Pope works it toward mid-wicket.
Drags his length back, once again, outside off. Ollie Pope chops it toward off side and gets a single.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR POPE! A fine shot to bring up his century! Pope has looked busy ever since his arrival and this is a well-deserved century. Short and wide outside off. Ollie Pope cuts it with full control and the ball rolls away toward the deep cover-point fence for a boundary.
Full-length delivery, on middle and leg. Joe Root flicks it toward deep square leg for one.
Pitches it up, on the stumps. Joe Root flicks it toward square leg.
Fuller, on off and middle. Joe Root pushes from his front foot toward mid on for no run.
Fuller, on off. Joe Root hangs back and pushes it toward mid on.
Fullish, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges and pushes it toward cover from the outer part of his willow.
FOUR! WELL PLAYED! Short, wide outside off. Ollie Pope rocks back, waits for it and opens the face of his willow to guide the delivery past the short third fielder for four runs.
Fuller, on the stumps. Ollie Pope eases it toward mid-wicket.

Fullish, around off. Ollie Pope drills it wide of the extra cover fielder, but the wide mid off fielder does well to track back and stops the rolling ball with the help of his left boot. A couple taken in between.
Pitches it up, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges and blocks it right under his eyes.
Short, on off and middle. Joe Root rocks back and punches it toward long on for a single.
Flighted, on off. Ollie Pope prods and knocks it toward mid on. A maiden over for Sikandar Raza!
Tossed up, on off. Ollie Pope hangs back and eases it toward mid off.
Fuller, on the stumps. Ollie Pope stabs it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, middle. Ollie Pope whips it toward mid-wicket.
Fuller, just outside off. Ollie Pope punches it hard but straight towards the hands of the cover fielder.
Flat and fuller, on off. Ollie Pope knocks it toward the right of the bowler.
Fuller, around the pads. Joe Root flicks it toward short fine leg.
Shortish, outside off. Joe Root guides it this time, toward the left of the third man fielder and gets a couple.
Fullish, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it toward cover and gets a single.
FOUR! Short and punished! Drags his length back, once again, outside off. Ollie Pope uses the depth of the crease and spanks it hard toward the sweeper cover fence for a boundary.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Joe Root clips it toward square leg. Crosses for a single.
FOUR! CRACKED! Short and outside off. Joe Root hangs back and punches it right from the middle of his bat toward deep cover-point for his first boundary of the inning.
Tossed up, on middle. Ollie Pope lunges and pushes it right of the bowler. Sikandar Raza does well to dive and make a stop.
Flatter and pitches it up, on the pads. Joe Root clips it toward deep square leg to take one.
Drags his length back, outside off. Ollie Pope cuts it toward deep backward point.
Fuller, outside off. Ollie Pope drills it straight to the hands of the cover fielder.
Short, on of and middle. Joe Root works it toward square leg. They cross.
Fuller, on middle, drifting it down the leg. Ollie Pope goes deep into the crease and flicks it off his pads toward square leg for one.
Pitched up, on off, Joe Root presses forward and just eases it away through covers for a couple of runs.
In the channel on off, on a back of a length, Joe Root dabs it with an open bat face towards gully where Brian Bennett dives to his right to make the stop.
A tempter for Root. Full and wide on off, Joe lets it be.
On a short of a length, on middle, Ollie Pope jabs it behind square on the leg side for one more.
Fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope drives it straight to cover.
On a back of a length, around off, Joe Root gets on his toes and pats it to deep point for a single.
Fired onto the pads on the fuller side, Ollie Pope misses the flick and wears it on the front pad.
Short and on off, Joe Root punches it wide of cover for a single to get off the mark.
Floated up, full and on off, worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Short and this drifts away slightly, outside off, Root steers it to backward point.
Shorter and slower, turning into the pads, Joe Root rocks back and tucks it to square leg.

OUT! LBW! A loud shout and the finger is raised! Zak Crawley has a word with his partner and takes the review. This looked straight in real time. Turning in fractionally, on a length, on middle, Zak goes for the full blooded sweep but misses as the ball sneaks under the bat and hits him on the front pad. UltraEdge shows no bat. It is three reds on Ball Tracking with the ball crashing into the leg stump. The on-field decision is upheld. Zimbabwean fans have something to cheer about. Crawley walks off to a standing ovation.
Zak Crawley lbw S Raza 124 (171b 14x4 0x6)
Full and outside off, driven sweetly but straight to cover.
FOUR! Easy as you like! On a back of a length, down leg, Ollie Pope swivels and helps it away to deep fine leg for a boundary.
On a length, on off, Ollie Pope checks his drive as he pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on the pads, Ollie Pope fails to help it away. The ball brushes his pads and rolls behind to the keeper.
Lands it on a short of a length, on middle, Ollie Pope misses the flick and gets beaten on the inside edge.
On a nagging length, outside off, Zak Crawley dabs it to deep point for a single.
Slower through the air, on off, Zak Crawley steers it through point for a single.
Short and wide on off, Zak Crawley thumps it hard but can't get it past the man at cover.
Short and on off, punched to cover.
Pushed through, around off, Ollie Pope presses forward and guides it through point for one.
Slows it down, on off, on a length, Zak Crawley taps it wide of point for one more.
Full and at the stumps, eased to long on for a single by Pope.
On off, on a length, blocked out with a straight bat.
On the off stump, kept out by Zak.

'Catch it' is the call but Zak Crawley manages to get it just over! Fuller in length, on off, Zak looks to go back over the bowler's head. Manages to evade the backtracking mid off fielder and collects a couple of runs. Crawley hobbles while returning for the second run. Looks like the blow he took on the right hip bone on the second ball of the over is causing him some discomfort.
On a length, on off, Zak Crawley defends it right under his eyes.
Drags the length back, over off, Zak Crawley sets up for the pull but gets an inside edge onto the hip.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Width offered and Zak Crawley cashes in! On a length, wide on off, Zak uses his reach to get his hands through the ball and creams the drive past the diving cover fielder for a boundary. Tanaka Chivanga has overstepped.
On a hard length, angling into the pads, Zak Crawley misses the flick and wears it high on the front pad.
Short and wide on off, Ollie Pope thumps it to the right of the man at deep point. The substitute fielder, Wellington Masakadza sprints and dives to his right to save the boundary. Two runs taken.
Tosses it up, full and on leg, Zak Crawley turns it through square leg for a run. 350 is up for England!
On the pads, flicked away behind square on the leg side for another single.
Short and on off, Zak Crawley punches it wide of cover for one more.
Tossed up, full and on middle, clipped away through mid-wicket for one.
Short and on middle, punched to mid on.
On a nagging length, on off, Zak Crawley waits back to block.
On a length, outside off, Zak Crawley reaches out and caresses it to the right of deep point for a couple.

FIVE WIDES! Tanaka Chivanga bends his back and digs it in short but this is way down leg. Zak Crawley lets it be. The keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga flings himself to his left but stands no chance as the ball evades him.
On a good length, on off, Zak Crawley pats it down the deck.

FOUR! Gets it through! Pitched up, on off, Zak Crawley extends his hands into the shot and firms the drive to the right of mid off. Victor Nyauchi is late to get the dive in and the ball goes under his body for a boundary.
On off, on a length, Zak Crawley is solid in defence.
Full and at the stumps, blocked out by Zak.
At 90 kph, on off, on a nagging length, dabbed through point for one.
Short and on the pads, Ollie Pope turns it away through square leg for one.
A real half-tracker, on middle, Ollie Pope goes on the back foot and slaps it but picks out the man at cover again.
Tosses it up, Ollie Pope drives but can't get it past cover.
Short and flat, on middle, Ollie Pope punches it to the right of the bowler.
On a nagging length, on off, Zak Crawley pushes it wide of cover for a single.
On a back of a length, on off, Ollie Pope waits on it and steers it late to the left of the man at deep backward point for a brace. The 100-run stand comes up between these two batters!
Fuller and on middle, Ollie Pope eases it to mid on.
Lands it on a length around the off stump, Ollie Pope defends.
Full and on off, Ollie Pope pushes it to mid off.
On the fuller side, outside off, driven to deep point for one.
On the pads, on a short of a length, Ollie Pope glances it down to deep fine leg for one.
Floated up, on the pads, clipped in front of deep mid-wicket for another single.

Attacking the stumps, slower and fuller, Zak Crawley brings out the reverse paddle and plays it fine towards deep third. The fielder in the deep runs around and cuts it off to prevent the boundary. Three runs taken.
Short and on middle, Ollie Pope punches it to long on and gets to the other end.
Slower and around off, on a length, Ollie Pope keeps it out on the off side.
On off, quicker, Ollie Pope goes back and pats it back to the bowler.
Short and on off, Zak Crawley guides it wide of backward point for one.
Slanting into the pads, on a short of a length, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full again, on off, driven to mid on.
On the fuller side, on off, Ollie Pope lunges to block.
Too straight again, on the pads, Ollie Pope flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs more.
SIX! Full and sliding onto the pads, Ollie Pope picks it up sweetly and hits it flat and to the left of deep backward square leg for a six.

A bit of a leading edge but that takes Zak Crawley to a HUNDRED! A quality knock from a quality batter and the Nottingham crowd rises as one to applaud the ton. On a nagging length, on off, Zak looks to turn it away on the leg side and closes the bat face early. Gets a soft leading edge that rolls through point for one.
Full and on off, clipped to mid-wicket.
A bit too short, on off, Ollie Pope punches it straight to cover.
On the pads, on a length, swept away to short fine leg.
On a nagging length, on off, Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Fired in, full and straight, knocked to long on for one by Zak.
Angling into the pads, on a nagging length, Ollie Pope wrists it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
On off, on a good length, Zak Crawley stabs it down on the off side.
FOUR! Glorious! A half-volley, outside off, Zak Crawley just eases himself into the drive and caresses it through covers for a boundary. Moves to 98.
On off, on a good length, Ollie Pope steers it wide of point for a single.
Ouch, that will hurt! On a nagging length, on off, Ollie Pope lunges to defend but the ball shoots up and goes on to hit the wrist watch of Pope.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ollie Pope! On a back of a length, on middle and leg, Pope gets on the back foot quickly and nails the pull through backward square leg for four more.

FOUR! Not in complete control but Pope will take it! Short and wide on off, Ollie Pope does not quite get on top of the bounce and throws his hands at the ball. A bit of extra bounce results in the ball catching the top edge and the ball sails over the man at gully for a boundary. 300 up for England!
Pushed through, on a nagging length, on middle and leg, jabbed to mid-wicket.
Short and on off, Ollie Pope punches it wide of cover for a single.
Turning into the pads, on a length, Ollie Pope paddles it to short fine leg.
Shorter and on the pads, Zak Crawley goes back and tucks it away wide of mid-wicket for a run.
FIFTY FOR POPE! An enterprising knock from Ollie so far and he will be keen to convert this into a big score. Tossed up, full and on off, eased to long on for a single.
Flat and short, on off, Ollie Pope pushes it to mid on off the back foot.

Uppish but Zak Crawley gets away with it! On a length, outside off, Crawley flays at the delivery well away from his body. Gets an outside edge that goes aerially but through the vacant backward point region. Ben Curran runs around in the deep to his left and cuts it off. Two runs taken. That will be TEA on Day 11
Full and on the pads, worked away to deep square leg for another single.
On off, on a short of a length, cut away to backward point.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Too straight, on the fuller side, Ollie Pope just glances it off the pads towards deep fine leg fence for a boundary.
In the channel on off, on a short of a length, kept out on the off side.
On a back of a length, on the pads, Zak Crawley works it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
This keeps straight, full and on the off stump, turned away to mid-wicket by Pope.
More loop on this one, around off, Ollie Pope reaches out in front to smother the spin.
Attacking the front pad, on a length, Ollie Pope tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and slower, on off, Ollie Pope gets on the front foot to defend.
This keeps a bit low, on a nagging length, on middle and leg, Ollie Pope pushes it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fractionally short, it is the leg break, around off, Ollie Pope presses back and cuts it to the right of point for a boundary.
Sliding onto the pads, on a length, tucked to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, on off, Zak Crawley punches it to cover-point.
On a good length, attacking the stumps, Zak Crawley waits back to block.
Pitched up, outside off, Zak Crawley checks the drive to short cover.
Lands it full, on off, Ollie Pope eases it to the left of extra cover for a single.
Bowls it full, outside off, Ollie Pope times the drive to cover.

Pushed through, on middle and leg, not all that short but Ollie Pope goes on the back foot and looks to play it to the left of short fine leg. Gets a top edge that goes through backward square leg for one.
Tosses it up, on off, Pope blocks it out.
Slows it down and this is fuller, on off, Ollie Pope defends it off the front foot.
A bit too short again but this stays low, outside off, Ollie Pope chops it out to backward point.
Short and around off, Ollie Pope waits on it and cuts it late to the left of backward point for a brace. The 50-run stand comes up.
Short and on middle, jabbed to mid-wicket.
Too full, on off, Ollie Pope squeezes it out off the inner half towards deep square leg for one more.
Lands it full, on off, defended with a straight bat.
Drags the length back and corrects the line, in the channel, Zak Crawley pats it wide of cover for another single.
On the pads, on a length, Ollie Pope flicks it through square leg for a run.
Full again, around off, Zak Crawley looks to push it through the off side. Gets it off the inner half past square leg for a single.
Full and on off, blocked out off the front foot.
Overpitched on off, Ollie Pope plays the push drive straight to short cover.
Full wrist spin delivery on middle, Zak Crawley flicks this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short again on off, Zak Crawley moves away to create some room and again pushes it straight to short cover.
Short off break on off, Zak Crawley punches it to short cover.
Full, leg break, on leg, Zak Crawley looks to flick it but doesn't get any bat as the ball hits front pad.
Quicker shorter on leg, Ollie Pope flicks it behind square for a single.

Full this time, angled in on off, Ollie Pope defends it off the front foot, as the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes to the right of short mid-wicket. Batters scamper through for a quick single.
Length ball around off, Zak Crawley pushes it to the left of short cover and picks up a single.
FOUR! That is a flashy pull shot! Short on middle, Zak Crawley plays the pull off the front foot, in front of square for a boundary.
A touch full on off, Zak Crawley defends it off the front foot to short cover.
Drags his length back a bit on this occasion does Blessing Muzarabani. The line is on middle, Ollie Pope works it behind square to the right of deep square leg for a single.
Length ball on off, Ollie Pope blocks it under his eyes.
Full on middle, Zak Crawley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Short on middle, Ollie Pope works it off the back foot to the deep square leg region for a single.
Full on off, Ollie Pope defends it off the front foot.
Short length outside off, Round armish from Sikandar Raza. Zak Crawley cuts it through covers to the deep extra cover fielder for a single.

Full and a touch quick on off, from Sikandar Raza as he sees Zak Crawley going for reverse sweep. Zak Crawley doesn't get any bat on it but thankfully for him, he somehow manages to get some glove on it. Else this would have been a goner.
Full on leg stump, Zak Crawley goes for the sweep, but doesn't get any bat on the ball, as the ball hits his front leg and goes into the ground.
FOUR! Innovation from Ollie Pope! Looks like he is in 'Bazball' mode! Bouncer on off, Ollie Pope upper cuts this one over the slip cordon for four.
Overpitched again around off, Ollie Pope drives this one to mid off. No run.
FOUR! Driven through covers! Ollie Pope has raced to 26 off just 16 balls! Full on off. Ollie Pope drives this smoothly through covers to pick up yet another boundary.
Length ball angled in and straightens a bit after pitching. The line though is quite outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Length ball swinging away, well outside off, Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Full on middle, Zak Crawley defends it into the off side and calls for one.
Shortish again on middle, Ollie Pope punches it to mid on. No run.
A touch short on middle leg, Zak Crawley works it off the back foot to deep square leg for a single.
A touch short and quick on middle, Ollie Pope cuts it along the ground to deep extra cover for a single.
Full, almost a full toss on off, Ollie Pope drives this to mid off. No run.
FOUR! Short and put away! Freebies on offer and Ollie Pope is not going to miss out on that! Short on off, Ollie Pope moves away a bit and cuts it through the extra cover region for four.
A touch short on off, Zak Crawley drives it off the crease to long off for a single.

A touch fuller and angled into the right hander, on middle off, Ollie Pope looks to drive it off the front foot, but the ball hits the inner half of the bat and ricochets onto his pads and drops onto the ground.
Full on leg, Ollie Pope flicks this one behind square to deep fine leg and picks up two runs.
FOUR! It is a risky shot but it's paid off for Ollie Pope! Length ball just outside off, Ollie Pope steers this one between gully and third slip for four.
Better from Blessing Muzarabani! Length ball, seaming away outside off, Ollie Pope shoulders his arms to that one.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Ollie Pope! Full on middle, Ollie Pope flicks this with ease, through the backward square leg region for four.
Back of a length on off, Ollie Pope hops a bit as he steers this one to the left of the deep point fielder for two runs.
Overpitched on middle, Ollie Pope drives this one, to long on for a single.
FOUR! Ollie Pope is off and running! Short and quick, around off, Ollie Pope is quick to rock back as he cuts it through the point region to pick up his first runs.

Some sharp turn for Wessly Madhevere! Short and quick, turning on leg. Ollie Pope is deceived by the turn as he looks to work it into the leg side and gets beaten. The ball hits his back pad. An appeal follows and not given. Sliding down leg, perhaps. Height was also an issue.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wessly Madhevere has the last laugh! Ben Duckett's superb knock comes to an end. Full and quick on off, Ben Duckett perhaps gets surprised by the extra pace as he just swings through the line and ends up slicing it straight in the hands of short cover where Ben Curran takes an easy catch.
Ben Duckett c B Curran b W Madhevere 140 (134b 20x4 2x6)
SIX! Now a big one! Short again, and Ben Duckett rocks back and pulls this one way over the deep mid-wicket fence for a big six.
FOUR! Short and outside off, enough width on offer, Ben Duckett cuts it in front of square through extra cover for four.
Fuller now, just outside off. Zak Crawley prods and drives but straight to the mid off fielder. Zak Crawley seems to feel disgusted for not finding a gap.
Hard-length delivery, angling away, Ben Duckett pushes it toward cover for one.
Tap and run! Short, just outside off. Zak Crawley hops a bit and taps it in front of the cover fielder to take a single.
Short, wide outside off. Zak Crawley isn't interested in offering anything to it.
Back of a length, once again just outside off. Ben Duckett opens the face of his bat and guides it toward deep backward point for rotating the strike.
Back of a length, just outside off. Ben Duckett covers the stumps and nudges the delivery toward the leg side.
Short, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley knocks it toward mid on for no runs.

FOUR! PURE CLASS! Full-length delivery, outside off, around the seventh stump. Zak Crawley plants his front foot toward the delivery and drives it past the cover fielder, toward the deep sweeper cover fence for his 10th boundary of the inning.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley gets on his toes and punches it toward the right of the deep point fielder for a brace.
Good-length delivery, angling it down the leg. Zak Crawley once again goes for a flick and misses.
Touch fuller, sprays it down the leg. Zak Crawley misses the flick.

FOUR LEG BYES! Nothing is clicking for Zimbabwe right now! Back of a length, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to pull but misses and the ball brushes his thigh pad and races toward the deep fine leg fence for a boundary.
Flatter, fuller, on leg. Ben Duckett works it toward square leg for no run.
FOUR! Dispatched! A half-tracker, on off, asking to be hit, Ben Duckett rocks back and thumps it to the left of cover for a boundary.
Slower and shorter, on off, Ben Duckett defends.
Ben backs away and Raza spots it. Follows the batter and Duckett can only push it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on the pads. Ben Duckett eases it back to the bowler.
Fuller, outside off. Ben Duckett blocks it back to the bowler.

Slower one now, just outside off. Ben Duckett crouches and lofts it up and over the bowler. The connection is not the cleanest, therefore the ball dies down around the fence at long on. Three runs taken.
Fuller on pads. Zak Crawley tucks it toward deep mid-wicket for a single.
200 up for England! Short, well wide outside off. Ben Duckett reaches toward the delivery to slap it toward deep point for a single.

FOUR BYES! Free runs for England! Short, pitching it wide outside off, but angles it in on off. Ben Duckett looks to pull but misses on the inner edge. The ball zips toward the right of the keeper and races away for four.
Short of a length, on off. Zak Crawley drags a pull toward deep square leg for one.
Fuller, on the pads. Zak Crawley clips it toward mid-wicket.
Short, outside off. Ben Duckett slaps it toward cover.
Fuller, on middle. Zak Crawley turns it towards deep square leg for one.

In the air...lands safely! Fuller, on off and middle. Ben Duckett walks down the track and attempts to nudge it toward leg side but closes his willow pretty early. The ball connects the leading edge and loops in front of the wide mid on fielder. The fielder has a chase to cover the ground and make an attempt but the ball is out of his reach.
Fuller, on pads. Ben Duckett clips it toward mid-wicket.
Short, on the stumps. Ben Duckett blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on leg. Zak Crawley pushes it toward deep square leg for one.

SIX! Up, up and over! The first one of the inning! Short of a length, once again from Tanaka Chivanga, on off and middle. Ben Duckett swats it uppishly to clear the deep square leg fence for half a dozen.
On a length, angling down the leg. Ben Duckett misses the heave and the delivery brushes his outer pad on the way toward the keeper.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Short, and wide outside off. Ben Duckett trusts the width of the delivery and spanks it hard toward the deep cover-point fence for another boundary.
Good-length delivery, pitching it just outside off and nips it in toward the off and middle. Ben Duckett nudges it toward square leg for no run.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Duckett hops and pushes it toward cover.
Back of a length, wide outside off with a pace of 138 kph. Ben Duckett extends his arm to offer a cut but misses on the outer edge.
Fuller, on the pads. Zak Crawley tucks it toward deep mid-wicket.

TWO LEG BYES! Fuller, spraying it down the leg. Zak Crawley clears his front foot to go a bit toward deep square leg but misses and hits his pad. The ball rolls toward deep fine leg and the batters get a couple.
Short, on stumps. Zak Crawley dabs it back to the bowler.
Flatter and fuller, on off. Ben Duckett flicks it toward long on for one.
Fuller, around off. Ben Duckett pushes it toward the off side.
Short, just outside off. Ben Duckett slaps it straight to the fielder in the cover region.
Bye! Going down leg with the angle, on a back of a length, Ben Duckett misses the tickle. The keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga dives and parries it away to his right. The batters cross over.
FOUR! More runs from Ben Duckett! On a length, around the hips of the batter. Ben Duckett clips it toward the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Fuller, outside off. Ben Duckett drives toward cover for no run.
A bit slower, on off. Ben Duckett pushes it back to the bowler uppishly. The ball drops just short of Victor Nyauchi.
On a length, on stumps. Ben Duckett eases it toward mid on.

FOUR! Ben Duckett is on fire! Short of a length, on off and middle. Ben Duckett hangs back and pulls it hard toward the right of the square leg fielder. Sikandar Raza flings himself to his right to take a one-handed blinder but the ball evades him and races away towards the boundary.
Tosses it up, on a length, on off, Zak Crawley lunges to block.
Pushed through, on a nagging length, on middle, Zak Crawley pushes it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! SHOT! Short, outside off. Zak Crawley stands tall and punches it wide of the cover fielder for four more runs.

HUNDRED for Ben Duckett! What a sensational piece of knock we have witnessed so far from him! Fuller delivery, on middle and leg. Ben Duckett flicks it toward square leg and gets the single to complete his fifth Test century. Takes the helmet off and soaks in all the applause from his home crowd.
Fuller, on middle once again. Ben Duckett blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Ben Duckett clips it toward the short fine leg fielder.
Fuller, on leg. Ben Duckett clips it toward deep square leg and takes a single to move to 99.
BEATEN! Fuller, wide outside off. Ben Duckett crouches and looks to lace it over the cover region but gets beaten on the outer edge.
Fuller, on off. Ben Duckett blocks it out.
That is certainly a good take from Tafadzwa Tsiga! Fuller, drifts down the leg. Ben Duckett misses his flick and Tsiga flies to his right to gather the ball one handed.
On a length, on pads. Zak Crawley clips it toward fine leg for one.
Fuller, on middle, shaping it toward the leg side. Ben Duckett flicks it toward the far right of the deep fine leg fielder and gets three runs between the sticks.
Touch fuller, on the stumps. Zak Crawley defends it toward his off side.
Fuller, outside off. Zak Crawley knocks it wide of the cover fielder for a brace.
Short, on off. Ben Duckett punches it toward long off for one.
FOUR! Excellent placement from Duckett! Short of a length, on off. Ben Duckett opens his stance and pushes the delivery toward the right of the diving cover fielder for four more runs.
Fuller, outside off. Zak Crawley comes down the track and pushes it toward long on for one.
Fuller, on middle. Zak Crawley turns it toward the right of the short mid-wicket fielder for no run.
Back of a length, on off. Ben Duckett hangs back, gets on his toes and blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, just outside off. Ben Duckett defends it right under his eyeline.
On a length, wide outside off. Ben Duckett comfortably cuts it toward the right of deep point for a couple of runs.
Much fuller, around the yorker length, outside off. Ben Duckett jams it toward off side.
Pitches it up, on stumps. Ben Duckett keeps it out.
On a length, angling away from the batter. Ben Duckett leaves it alone.
FOUR! 12 runs from the over! An expensive one for Sikandar Raza! Fuller, on off. Zak Crawley gets down on one knee and sweeps it toward the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Ben Duckett drives it toward cover for one.
Flatter and fuller, outside off. Ben Duckett makes use of his front foot and drills it toward sweeper cover for a couple.

FOUR! A bit of innovation coming out from Ben Duckett! Sikandar Raza tossed it up, on off. Ben Duckett reverse sweeps the delivery past the short third fielder and gets four more runs added to his account.
Fuller, sprays it down the leg. Zak Crawley flicks it toward deep square leg and gets a single.

FOUR! Fortuitous boundary for Ben Duckett! Angling in and then nipping away from around the wicket, on a back of a length, Ben is forced to play it. Presents a straight bat to keep it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes in the gap between second slip and gully for a boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Ben Duckett hangs back and pats it toward cover.
Fuller in length, on off, Ben Duckett plays it back to the bowler.
On a good length, on off, defended on the off side.
Pitched up, on off, Ben Duckett mistimes the drive to cover.

Appeal goes round for caught behind but the umpire says no! Tafadzwa Tsiga, behind the stumps, seems confident but the bowler walks back to his stance. There's a bit of discussion between the keeper and the skipper but they decide not to take the review. Back of a length, pitching it just outside off and then straightening. Ben Duckett plays it inside the line and the ball zips past the outside edge. The replays show that the ball brushed the jumper Duckett is wearing, on its way to the keeper.
Drags his length back, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley dabs it toward his leg side.
Pitches it up, outside off. Ben Duckett drives it gently toward long off for one.
Fuller on middle. Zak Crawley flicks it toward square leg for one.
Flatter, outside off. Ben Duckett plays it toward long off for one.
Excellent stop from Brian Bennett! Short, outside off. Ben Duckett cuts it towards cover where Bennett puts a dive and makes a stop.
Sikandar Raza jogs from around the wicket and bowls it full, just outside off. Ben Duckett pushes it toward the right of the bowler.
Well wide on off, on a good length, Zak Crawley lets it be. That will be LUNCH on Day 1!
Another one that swings back into the right-hander but the line is down leg, Zak Crawley misses the tickle.

A loud shout for LBW but turned down! That seemed to be doing too much. Zimbabwe think about it and eventually decide against the review. This moves back in the air, on a length, Zak Crawley is beaten on the flick and wears it on the knee roll on the front pad. A wise decision not to go for the review as the Ball Tracking shows that the ball would have missed the leg stump.
Bowled from wide of the crease, this tails back in, on a length, on off, Zak Crawley presents a straight bat and knocks it to mid on.
On the pads again, on a good length, Ben Duckett shovels it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Sliding down the leg side from around the wicket, on a length, Ben Duckett fails to help it away.
On middle and leg, on a short of a length, nudged through square leg for one more.
On a hard length, on off, Ben Duckett gets on the back foot and dabs it down.
Fractionally wide on off, on a short of a length, Ben Duckett waits on it and guides it towards deep backward point. Ben Curran sprints and dives to his right to save the boundary. Two runs taken.
Slanting into the right-hander, on a length, on middle, Zak Crawley plants his front foot ahead and wrists it to deep square leg for one.
On a good length, around off, Zak Crawley plays it late and dabs it to backward point.
Full and on off, driven to the left of the bowler.
On off, on a back of a length, Ben Duckett steers it with an open bat face to the right of deep backward point for a brace.
Delivers it on a good length, on off, Ben Duckett waits back to defend.
FOUR! Gets it through! Fuller in length, outside off, Ben Duckett does not quite hold of it on the drive. The ball goes through the tumbling Sikandar Raza at cover-point for four.
Seaming in, on a nagging length, on off, Zak Crawley tucks it behind square on the leg side for one more.
On a back of a length, on off, whipped wide of mid-wicket for one.
Attacking the stumps from around the wicket, Ben Duckett covers the line and blocks it out.
Lovely! Full and outside off, Zak Crawley is lured into the false shot as he plays it away from his body. Goes for the drive and gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball moves away.
Full and on off, Zak Crawley pushes it back to the bowler.
Pitched up, around the off stump, Ben Duckett does not move his feet much and just goes at it with hands as he looks to drive it down the ground. Gets an outside edge wide of point for one.
On top of off, on a short of a length, Ben Duckett stabs it down on the off side.

FOUR! Not exactly where Ben Duckett intended but he will take it! Short and well wide on off, Ben reaches out and gets it off right off the toe end. Beats the diving gully fielder to his left for a four.
Bashes the hard length, angling into the pads, Ben Duckett hops to flick it away but misses and wears it high on the front pad.

FIFTY FOR CRAWLEY! Just the start to the summer, Zak would have wanted and England will hope that this is just the first of many. A bit too straight, on the pads, on a length, Crawley turns it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Sliding down leg, on a length, Zak Crawley misses the tickle.
Jagging back in, on off, on a good length, Zak Crawley stays back to keep it out.
Tightens the line, on a nagging length, not that wide for the cut but Ben Duckett goes for it. Chops it down in front of cover for one.
FOUR! Put away with ease! On a back of a length, width offered on off, Ben Duckett waits back and slaps it past cover for a boundary.
Going across, on a good length, Ben Duckett lets it be.
Short, outside off. Ben Duckett cuts it toward deep cover for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley punches it toward deep point for one.
Short of a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley pulls it across the line toward deep mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Fuller, well outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.

Huge round of applause from the Nottingham crowd as England reach the 100-run mark! Back of a length, wide outside off. Zak Crawley rides the bounce and steers it toward deep backward point to get the brace.
On a length, around the hips of the batter. Ben Duckett hops and clips it toward square leg for one.
Fuller, wide outside off. Zak Crawley attempts to smash it toward the cover region but misses it with a large gap.
Good length, just outside off. Zak Crawley blocks it away.

FOUR! Excellent shot! It certainly looked like Zak Crawley was a bit hurried but he reacted very quickly! Short in length, shaping it down the leg. Zak Crawley swivels and goes for a pull toward the far right of the deep backward square leg fielder for four more runs.
Fuller, on the pads. Zak Crawley clips it toward mid-wicket for no run.
Back of a length, around the hips of the batter. Ben Duckett tucks it toward his leg side for one.
That one kept low! Fuller one, outside off. The ball skids low after pitching on the track. Ben Duckett blocks it from the toe end of his bat.
Pitches it up, outside off. Zak Crawley pushes it toward cover.
Back of a length, pitching it just outside off and shaping it in. Zak Crawley once again lifts his willow and makes a leave.
Fuller, around off. Zak Crawley crunches a drive but straight to the extra cover fielder.
Back of a length, well wide outside off. Zak Crawley lifts his willow high and lets this one through.
Short of a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Good start from Blessing Muzarabani! Bowls it on a length, just outside off and the ball straightens after pitching. Zak Crawley plays inside the line and gets beaten.
Fuller, down the leg. Ben Duckett once again misses the flick. Ben Duckett has to be more careful with those deliveries.
Full, on the pads, shaping it in. Ben Duckett flicks and misses. Half an appeal from the bowler but it is clearly going down the leg.

Excellent effort from Ben Curran! Full-length delivery, nipping it in toward the middle and leg. Ben Duckett flicks it toward the right of the square leg fielder. Curran dives and makes a one-handed stop.
Short, wide outside off. Zak Crawley slaps it toward deep point for one.
On a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley pushes it toward cover.
Fuller, just outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend it toward his off side but gets beaten on the outer edge.

FOUR! FIFTY for Ben Duckett! It's in a streaky way, but he will take those runs! Back of length from Tanaka Chivanga shaping it across the batter. Ben Duckett looks to heave it across the line but gets a thick outside edge. The ball loops over the slips and goes for a boundary. Duckett lifts his bat up and soaks up all the cheers from the spectators!
Fuller, around off. Ben Duckett mistimes his drive toward mid off.
Tap and run! Fuller, just outside off. Zak Crawley taps it in front of cover and gets a single.
Another shorter delivery, on the stumps. Ben Duckett pulls it toward square leg for one.
Short, just outside off. Ben Duckett blocks it out.
Yorker, on off. Zak Crawley tries to dig it out but gets the inner edge. The ball zips past the leg stump, toward fine leg. They cross for a single.
On a length, on leg. Zak Crawley tucks it toward square leg for one.

FOUR! More runs for England! Overpitched, on off stump. Zak Crawley gets forward and drives it toward the long off fence for a boundary. There is a fielder at the mid off region, but he has been placed a bit wide, more towards extra cover.
On a length, around off. Ben Duckett looks to dab it toward his leg side but gets a thick outer edge and the ball rolls toward point. Batters gets a single.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! Fuller delivery from Richard Ngarava, on middle, shaping it in towards the left hander. Ben Duckett just eases it toward the left of the bowler. The ball races away toward the long on fence and Ben gets a boundary.
Touch fuller, just outside off. Ben Duckett blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, sprays it down the leg. Ben Duckett looks to flick it but misses.
Short, around off. Zak Crawley blocks it toward his off side.

FOUR! This is Zak Crawley at his best! Pitches it up, wide outside off. Zak Crawley plants his front foot, leans on the delivery and drives it gently in the gap in the cover region for four more runs.
Some movement on the delivery now! On a length, pitching it outside off, around the seventh stump, nipping it away from the right-hander. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
NO BALL! Back of a length, just outside off. Ben Duckett punches it toward deep point. They cross. Tanaka Chivanga has overstepped and the umpire calls it a no ball.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Ben Duckett looks to drill it but fails to get the middle of the willow. The ball rolls toward mid off for no run.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley prods and pushes it toward cover to take another single.
Tanaka Chivanga scoots from over the wicket and bowls right into the blockhole, outside off. Duckett crouches a bit and jams it toward the vacant space in the cover region for a single.
Full and wide outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Full on off, Zak Crawley drives it straight to mid off.

FOUR! A touch fuller, angled across, outside off, Zak Crawley drives this along the ground to the left of short cover, where Ben Curran dives to his left, but doesn't manage to save the ball, as the ball goes through him for four.
Length ball, tails back into the right hander, on middle, Zak Crawley hops on the back foot and punches it to point.
Length ball, with a hint of shape into the right hander, outside off. Zak Crawley judges the line well and leaves it alone.
Length ball, angling away, outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Length ball moving away on middle, Zak Crawley looks to push it down the ground, as the ball hits the inside half off the bat and goes to short mid-wicket. Batters sneak in a single.
Full and on off, driven sweetly but straight to cover.
Full on middle, a bit of shape again. Ben Duckett flicks it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.

Wow! This time the ball goes the other way. Length ball, just outside off. Zak Crawley drives through the line and connects thin air as the ball goes through the bat pad gap. The wicket-keeper dives to his left and manages to get a hand on it, but couldn't collect it properly. The batters sneak in a single.
Full and swinging away, wide outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone. Tafadzwa Tsiga, the wicket-keeper, dives to his right and collects it one-handed. Good take.
Full on middle, Ben Duckett clips it along the ground to deep square leg. Single taken.
Full and sliding down leg, Zak Crawley looks to flick it, but can't get any bat on it. Maiden over, that!
The in ducker! Length ball that seams into the right hander on middle. Zak Crawley is beaten by the movement as the ball hits him near the thigh guard area.
Length ball, outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Zak Crawley takes a step towards the bowler, and hence Blessing Muzarabani drags his length back. Zak Crawley eventually ends up guiding the ball to point.
Length ball on off, Zak Crawley defends it to point.
Length ball, in the channel of uncertainty, hint of shape away. Zak Crawley initially wanted to play at it but eventually gets his bat out of the way.
Overpitched on off, Ben Duckett drives it back to the bowler. No run.

FOUR! Third boundary of the over! Back of a length on the body. That one hurried Ben Duckett a bit as he goes for the pull and manages to get a bit of glove on that one. The ball runs away fine of the deep fine leg fielder who had no chance to cut it off.
Inswinging yorker on off, Ben Duckett digs it out as he pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ben Duckett! Length ball on leg, Ben Duckett clips it in the gap between deep square leg and deep fine leg for four.

FOUR! This boundary brings up the 50 for England! Full again and again good movement into the left hander, on middle. Ben Duckett is ready for it as he flicks it crisply through the mid-wicket region for four.
Full and shaping back into the left hander, on middle. Ben Duckett drives it back to the bowler.
Good length, and again the line is well outside off. Zak Crawley doesn't bother offering a shot to that one. End of the over.
Length ball, shaping away this time. But the line is well outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off, shaping in a hint, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle, Zak Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Zak Crawley gently pushes it to square leg. No run.
FOUR! Lovely from Zak Crawley! No need to run for those. Full on off, Zak Crawley drives this one the up, through covers for four.
FOUR! Pulled away! Attempted short ball on off, Ben Duckett is ready for it, as he crunches the pull shot with full control along the ground, to deep square leg fence, for four.
Length ball that rises a bit off a length, just outside off, Ben Duckett pushes it towards short cover.

Good length delivery with a hint of shape into the right hander, on off, Zak Crawley just taps into the off side and sets off for a quick single. The short cover fielder runs in front, towards the ball, but batters were quick enough to complete the single.
Good length, just outside off, Zak Crawley pushes it off the back foot, straight to point.
Overpitched on middle, Ben Duckett drives it along the ground past the mid on fielder for a single.

Oh! Almost the first wicket! Length ball, on off, Zak Crawley looks to push it into the off side, the ball takes the inside edge and ricochets onto his toes. That would have easily gone onto hit the stumps. Batters sneak in a quick single as Ben Duckett makes the call for one.
A harmless length delivery outside off, Ben Duckett looks to cut it, but doesn't get it off the middle, as the ball takes the under edge and goes on the bounce to the wicket-keeper.
Length delivery on leg, Ben Duckett works it behind square to the right of deep fine leg and picks up two runs.

Beauty from Blessing Muzarabani! Back of a length angling into the left hander, just outside off, and then straightens a touch as it whizzles past the outside edge of Ben Duckett's bat who tried to poke at it.

FOUR! More runs for Ben Duckett! Length ball on middle, Ben Duckett works it through the square leg region as the ball races along the turf and eventually wins the race against the short mid-wicket fielder who put in a good chase, but couldn't save the boundary.
Back of a length, outside off, Ben Duckett punches it to short cover.
FOUR! Crunched through covers! Full, outside off, Ben Duckett drives this one on the up through covers and picks up a boundary.

FOUR! Zak Crawley won't miss out on this! Full and angling across, a half volley with a lot of width on offer, Zak Crawley crouches a bit and leans into the drive as he hits sweetly through the extra cover region for four.
Full, angling away a touch on off, Zak Crawley drives it crisply off the middle of the bat, but ends up hitting it straight to short cover.
Legnth delivery, around off, Ben Duckett pushes it to short cover and sets off for a quick single.

Richard Ngarava drags his length back a bit, as he bowls a short of length ball, on off, Ben Duckett looks to pull it but doesn't quite get a good part of the bat on it as the ball hits the under edge and goes into the ground.
Length ball on middle, Ben Duckett defends it under his eyes as the ball goes to mid on.
Full and swinging away,outside off, Ben Duckett drives this through the cover point region and picks up two runs.

Delivered from wide of the crease, angling in on a length on off, Zak Crawley is beaten by the movement as he fails to bring his bat down in time. The ball hits him near the thigh guard area. A bit of an appeal for LBW but that is too high.

Dropped! Is it? Fuller on off, Zak Crawley drives it uppishly to the left of Blessing Muzarabani who puts his left hand out, but doesn't get any hand on it. He was completing the follow up after delivering the ball and hence it wasn't an easy chance by any means. The ball goes down the ground as the mid off fielder chases it. Two runs taken.
Length ball, angling into the right hander, on middle leg, Zak Crawley flicks it to short mid-wicket. No run.
Length ball angling into the right hander, on middle, Zak Crawley plays the push to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Zak Crawley pushes it off the crease, to short cover.
From round the wicket, length ball angling into the left hander, on middle, Ben Duckett flicks it behind square to deep fine leg for a single.
Full and swinging into the right hander on middle, Zak Crawley drives it back to the bowler.
Almost a yorker, angling outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Full and angling across the right hander, outside off, Zak Crawley drives it along the ground through covers for two runs.
Length ball, with a hint of movement into the left hander, on middle, Ben Duckett flicks it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
A touch full, outside off, Ben Duckett looks to drive it down the ground, but doesn't quite middle it and ends up hitting it back to the bowler.
Length ball shaping away, in the channel outside off, Ben Duckett looks to cut it and gets beaten on the outside edge.

Length ball that angles into the right hander, in the channel of uncertainty, and then straightens a touch as it leaves the right hander on its way to the wicket-keeper. Zak Crawley looks to defend it off the front foot and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball on off,  Zak Crawley defends it to mid off.
FOUR! Shot! Short ball from Blessing Muzarabani. Zak Crawley is up for it as he pulls it behind square in the vacant deep backward square leg region for four.
Good length ball on off, Zak Crawley works it to short mid-wicket.

Good delivery, this! Length ball, on middle, that seams into the right hander, as it comes in a long way. Zak Crawley looks to flick it but gets hit on the back pad. Appeal for LBW not given. Height is the issue.
Fuller, angling in on middle, Zak Crawley defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on middle, Ben Duckett defends it solidly off the front foot to mid on.
Length delivery, moving away slightly, just outside off, Ben Duckett comfortably plays it off the crease as he guides it to gully.
Good length ball swinging into the left hander, on off, Ben Duckett drives it again towards the short point fielder. No run.
A touch fuller on off, Ben Duckett drives it straight to short cover. He didn't middle that one.
Now the ball goes other way. Length ball swinging away, outside off, Ben Duckett guides it along the ground to gully.
Length ball, swinging into the left hander, around off, Ben Duckett defends it off the crease, back to the bowler.
Full again, angling in a bit, on middle, Zak Crawley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Full on off, Zak Crawley drives this as straight as an arrow, but unfortunately for him, the ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end.

A touch full again, outside off, a bit of shape into the left hander, Ben Duckett drives it off the front foot to the right of the short cover fielder, who dives and saves potentially three runs. Batters take one.
Full on middle, Zak Crawley flicks it in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket. The short mid-wicket fielder runs behind the ball and cuts it off well inside the ropes. Batters run three.
Overpitched on off, Zak Crawley drives it back to the bowler.
Length ball, moving slightly into the right hander on off, Zak Crawley defends it solidly under his eyes.
Full and swinging away, well outside off, Ben Duckett goes feeling at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.

That's more like it. Richard Ngarava now goes a touch fuller, the ball nips back into the left hander, on off, Ben Duckett is beaten by the movement, as he looks to defend it and the ball sneaks past his inside edge to hit the back pad. Appeal for LBW follows. Not given. Perhaps too high.
FOUR! Ben Duckett is off and running! Back of a length again, outside off, providing width, Ben Duckett flat bats it through covers for four. Richard Ngarava needs to be fuller here.
A touch fuller, swinging away a touch, just outside off, Ben Duckett cautiously blocks it under his eyes.
Another back of a length ball on leg, Zak Crawley tucks it behind square to the deep fine leg region for a single to get off the mark.
Richard Ngarava starts with a short of a length delivery on middle, Zak Crawley pushes it off the back foot, into the leg side to the right of short mid-wicket.
